<TEXT>
three members of the secret services 
uniformed division at the white house have been placed on 
administrative leave and two national security council employees 
were fired in a cocaine investigation officials said wednesday 
night 
the investigation involving drug use by workers at the white 
house has been going on for several months and is continuing said 
robert r snow spokesman for the secret service 
liz murphy a white house spokeswoman said two nsc clerical 
employees admitted drug use and were separated from the nsc 
the president is aware of this investigation she said 
presidential spokesman marlin fitzwater quoted in thursdays 
editions of the washington post said the white house was told 
there were no breaches of security found in connection with the 
nsc workers 
we are advised at this time that there was no sale or use on 
white house grounds fitzwater said 
fitzwater and murphy declined to describe the duties of the two 
women who worked at the nsc we cannot provide other details of 
the investigation which is still continuing said murphy 
snow said the drug enforcement administration was brought into 
the investigation after there were allegations that there was 
drug use among some members of the uniformed division he said 
information has been turned over to the us attorney for the 
district of columbia who is considering criminal prosecution 
no arrests have been made snow said these are only 
administrative actions at this point the three have been place 
on leave with pay two of them last friday and the third on monday 
he said 
snow would not say whether the workers were suspected of using 
cocaine at the white house or while on duty 
the us attorney is reviewing the case and im not going to 
get into specifics he said 
uniformed members of the secret service are assigned to guard 
the white house grounds the vice presidents home and foreign 
embassies they also travel with the president on trips to provide 
security 
snow said it was the first time he could recall action being 
taken against secret service officers over drug abuse allegations 
