a 2yearold brazilian girl adopted in 
israel after being kidnapped from her parents when she was 4 months 
old left for home wednesday after the supreme court ordered her 
returned 
twoyearold bruna wearing a green dress and a white necklace 
smiled at a crowd of journalists who watched her leave with her 
biological parents rosilda goncalves and luiz vasconselos of 
curitiba brazil 
the child was adopted by an israeli couple simone and yaacov 
turgeman who said they did not know she was kidnapped 
the turgemans did not go to tel avivs ben gurion international 
airport but turgeman stood on the balcony of his nearby home to 
see the plane take off israel army radio reported 
earlier this month israels supreme court ordered bruna 
returned to her biological parents 
it is wonderful to be going home with her i am the happiest 
man alive vasconselos said as the family stopped over at 
londons heathrow airport before continuing their trip to sao 
paulo brazil where a gala reception and parade were prepared for 
brunas homecoming thursday 
it is a wonderful day for us we are so very very happy and 
relieved said ms goncalves 
accompanying the family on the flight was roger cook a british 
television reporter whose investigative program the cook 
report uncovered brunas story during a probe of the 
international business of abducting and selling babies 
cook said he felt some sympathy for the adoptive parents who 
paid 25000 for bruna and named her carolyn they said they did 
not know she was an abducted baby and believed the money was needed 
to finalize adoption forms 
according to israel television a serious rift erupted between 
the couples over the weekend prompting the turgemans to file a 
supreme court appeal seeking an extension of the deadline however 
they withdrew the appeal monday 
for the first time since the transition period started bruna 
spent tuesday night with her biological parents israel army radio 
said 
turgeman said he met with the biological parents on tuesday to 
tell them not to forget that the child has four parents and not 
only two they are very interested in maintaining a link with us 
cook whose program is made for birminghambased central 
independent television said he and his researchers were told that 
over one border point between brazil and paraguay alone some 400 
babies a month were being illegally transported for sale 
