commission to crack down on fraud in telemarketing sales over the 
telephone which is estimated to cost consumers at least 1 
billion a year 
by a voice vote the house passed a measure on tuesday directing 
the ftc to draft rules governing sales by telephone and to make it 
easier to sue telemarketing companies 
the bill says the agency should consider including provisions 
that establish refund rights for customers and a period during 
which consumers can withdraw their order and set a time of day when 
unsolicited calls can be made 
the ftc estimates that telemarketing sales in 1986 amounted to 
more than 100 billion the agency however has been able to get 
back only about 25 million for defrauded consumers over the past 
four years rep thomas luken dohio said 
no piece of legislation is going to end fraud luken said 
during debate on the bill monday but i think this bill will 
significantly reduce the losses now being suffered by american 
consumers 
