<TEXT>
the english language diminishes 
nationalism among filipinos and tends to turn them into stammering 
secondrate people says a committee ordered by the senate to list 
the qualities of filipinos 
the committees report says a colonial mentality selfishness 
lack of discipline lack of initiative and lack of selfanalysis 
are major weaknesses of filipinos 
it says some of these traits are extremes of filipinos better 
qualities which include caring for others strong family ties 
humor religiosity industry and adaptability 
the report released tuesday was prepared by social scientists 
from the university of the philippines and the jesuitrun ateneo 
university it blames some of the countrys ills on the countrys 
colonial past 
the islands were ruled by spain for more than 300 years until 
the united states took over in 1898 the americans through a 
public education system patterned after their own imparted to 
filipinos the english language 
but the report says the use of english in this country of more 
than 7000 islands and about 80 indigenous languages and dialects 
has caused more harm than good 
english as the medium of education has defilipinized the 
youth and taught them to regard american culture as superior the 
report says 
thinking in our native language but expressing ourselves in 
english results not only in a lack of confidence but also in a lack 
of power of expression imprecision and stunted development of 
ones intellectual powers we ought to use filipino in our 
cultural and intellectual life and filipino should be the medium 
of instruction in all levels of education the report adds 
filipino or tagalog now is the medium of instruction in grade 
school and part of high school but english remains the main medium 
in college 
at the prodding of sen leticia ramos shahani the 23member 
senate directed its committees on education and social justice last 
september to conduct a study on ways of arresting philippine 
societys moral decay 
it said in a resolution that despite hopes of change immediately 
after the february 1986 people power revolution that sent 
president ferdinand marcos into exile graft and corruption 
nepotism lack of patriotism passivity and increasing crime 
continue to plague society 
these social ills instead of being mere memories from the 
past seem to have become even more ingrained in the character of 
the filipino so much so that many have commented that the 
problem has become endemic the resolution said 
mrs shahani said that the report entitled a moral recovery 
program building a people building a nation was the result of 
nine months of research including a nationwide survey of 2000 
people 
philippine society right now is sick mrs shahani said 
we are a society in crisis there are so many silent emergencies 
happening 
the report says filipinos desire to put family ahead of the 
common good is often the root of corruption and abuse of economic 
and political power 
and it says filipinos depend too much on authority and generally 
do not move until told what to do 
filipinos tend to be complacent and there rarely is a sense of 
urgency about any problem the report goes on there is a high 
tolerance for inefficiency poor service and even violations of 
ones basic rights 
in many ways it can be said that the filipino is too patient 
too easily resigned to his fate filipinos are thus easily 
oppressed and exploited 
the report says one way of solving the slide in morality is for 
both government and business leaders to be models of the positive 
traits of the filipino 
it suggests public and private offices organize national 
reflection weekends and encourage employees to attend them 
voluntarily 
on the problem of colonial mentality it says the countrys 
history must be taught from our perspective and the government 
should embark on education programs to instill patriotism and 
national pride 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

