and it was restated today so there wont be any confusion 
euthanasia is wrong and the medical profession will continue to 
deplore it 
the delegates also are considering a proposal to organize a new 
class of hospital bedside worker called a registered care 
technologist in an effort to offset the nursing shortage 
as envisioned in the doctors proposal these workers would 
receive from two months to 18 months of training and would handle 
such chores as bathing patients taking vital signs and changing 
bandages 
the plan is opposed by the american nurses association which 
says the answer to the shortage is increased salaries and better 
working conditions 
