would save less than 775 a year under the liberal democratic 
partys tax reform 
the association said the typical family would pay 1250 less in 
income and property taxes but a new 3 percent sales tax would cost 
an additional 475 
small businesses oppose the plan saying there is no guarantee 
they can pass on increased costs to consumers consumers have 
objected saying there is no guarantee prices wont rise 
substantially 
takeshitas plan calls for reducing the current 12 tax brackets 
with tax rates ranging from 105 percent to 60 percent to five 
brackets with rates ranging from 10 to 50 percent property taxes 
also would be reduced 
although tax revenues would drop at first they are expected to 
rise as the economy continues to expand boosted in part by 
takeshitas pledge to turn japan away from its exportdriven 
economy and increase domestic demand 
