<TEXT>
the united states and israel agreed wednesday 
to work together on the development of a new tactical missile 
designed to shoot down arab ballistic rockets which could be fired 
at israeli population centers 
israeli defense minister yitzhak rabin called the arrow project 
a response to pushbutton warfare in which arab foes were 
relying on soviet and chinese rockets to try pierce israeli 
defenses 
he said the missile should be ready for testing in two to three 
years with a decision on production depending on the results 
the agreement was signed at a pentagon ceremony by maj gen 
david ivry director general of the israeli defense ministry and 
lt gen james abrahamson who is in charge of the us strategic 
defense initiative 
israel is collaborating with the united states in the search for 
a spacebased defense against soviet ballistic missiles the 
program known popularly as star wars anticipates using kinetic 
energy lasers and other sophisticated technology to destroy the 
rockets before they could reach their us targets 
rabin stressed in a speech at the national press club that 
israels objectives were much more limited he said if the arrow 
proved effective in the tests the missile might be used as a 
defensive weapon at shortrange 
the israeli official said israel had to find a way to cope with 
the new missiles the soviets had supplied to syria and the chinese 
to saudi arabia he said the syrian missiles could reach almost 
every target in israel 
for the arabs who have fought six major wars with israel since 
1948 the rockets offer a chance to accomplish what arab armies and 
air forces could not achieve rabin said 
defense secretary frank c carlucci at a separate news 
conference said the arrow would make a contribution to our sdi 
program and have application as well in other areas 
he said the joint project fits in very well with our concept 
of deterrence based on defense 
secretary of state george p shultz who appeared with carlucci 
at the windup of separate talks with australian officials said 
if you happen to be sitting in israel with shorterrange 
ballistic missiles around you that are very hard to defend against 
you feel very strongly the importance of learning how to defend 
yoursevles against them 
a pentagon statement said 80 percent of the cost would be borne 
by the united states and 20 percent by israel 
the signing followed a statement of concern tuesday by president 
reagan after a meeting at the white house with rabin the president 
said he was troubled by ominous new military developments in 
the area 
rabin during two days of talks here has stressed soviet 
deliveries of new missiles to syria and libya and chinese 
shipments to saudi arabia 
if the united states could not persuade china and saudi 
arabia i doubt israel would be able to persuade the soviet 
union to refrain from the deliveries rabin said 
israel has had a series of diplomatic meetings recently with 
soviet officials that indicate a warming by moscow to the jewish 
state with which it broke relations in 1967 
on another subject rabin criticized american television 
networks and other media for giving much less coverage to missile 
attacks by iran and iraq on each others cities and other war 
atrocitiies than to the beatings of palestinian arabs on the west 
bank 
rabin said he was used to having a doublestandard applied 
to israel but he believed the networks should have devoted more 
than a few minutes to what he said was the slaying of 5000 kurds 
by iraq with chemical weapons 
