<TEXT>
the carbomb killing of a us defense 
attache here has again focused attention on greeces elusive 
terrorist group november 17 
the leftwing group has claimed responsibility for 12 political 
assassinations in 13 years including those of three american 
diplomats not one of its members has ever been arrested 
in a country where there is little violent crime november 17 
has gained notoriety for its bold attacks some in daylight in the 
center of athens 
besides us diplomats and servicemen its targets have included 
four greek police officers a conservative newspaper publisher and 
two prominent industrialists 
the conservative opposition has claimed that premier andreas 
papandreous panhellenic socialist movement pasok has link with 
terrorists making the government reluctant to crack down on local 
extremists 
the suspicion that pasok members relations with terrorists of 
every kind prevent the state from taking action is constantly being 
reinforced said the conservative new democracy party after 
november 17 claimed responsibility for killing greek industrialist 
alexandros athanassides in march 
us navy capt william e nordeen 51 died tuesday when a 
parked car containing more than 88 pounds of high explosives blew 
up next to his armorplated vehicle near his home in athens 
kifissia suburb 
police said the bomb was set off by a remotecontrol device and 
called it the most sophisticated attack yet staged by november 17 
as is its custom the group took responsibility in a lengthy 
statement sent to a leftwing athens daily a senior police 
officer speaking on condition of anonymity said the statement was 
hammered out on the same typewriter used for previous proclamations 
by the group 
the statement called for greece to pull out of the north 
atlantic treaty organization and shut down four us military bases 
here it said it would keep targeting americans until the last 
american soldier leaves greece 
november 17 is named for the date in 1973 that the rightwing 
military dictatorship then in power crushed a student rebellion at 
athens polytechnic university 
the organizations antiamerican profile reflects a belief still 
held by many greeks that us tolerance of the military regime 
enabled it to stay in power from 196774 
greeks also blame the united states for failing to prevent the 
1974 turkish invasion of cyprus after a coup there inspired by the 
athens junta 
speculation has been widespread among conservative politicans 
and newspapers that november 17 may have links with socialists who 
belonged to the panhellenic liberation movement 
papandreou founded panhellenic liberation a resistance 
organization when he was living in exile in sweden during military 
rule in greece he returned to greece in 1974 several of the 
resistance groups members including high ranking officials in the 
present government reportedly trained in palestinian camps in the 
early 1970s 
in the past the papandreou government has been sharply 
criticized by the united states for being lax in fighting 
terrorism but greece is now anxious to shake that image and 
deputy premier agamemnon koutsogiorgas on tuesday pledged tough 
and unrelenting measures against terrorist activity 
it is not known whether november 17 has any links with foreign 
terror groups but in the past police have speculated the group 
might have had contacts with italys red brigade and the frances 
direct action 
tuesdays carbomb attack triggered speculation among western 
diplomats that the group had been in touch with international 
terror groups skilled in such techniques november 17 used to 
specialize in attacks by gunmen on motorbikes using a 45 caliber 
pistol in their attacks 
athens cia station chief richard welch in 1975 and us navy 
capt george tsantes in 1983 were killed with the same 45 weapon 
according to police ballistics experts 
in the past senior greek police officers said they had a 
fingerhold on members of november 17 
but the closest they seem to have come was the october 1986 
discovery of a cache of weapons in the home of leftwinger michael 
prekas prekas was killed in a shootout with police and the 
investigation apparently reached another dead end 
