michael dukakis screened vice presidential running mates on 
wednesday telling reporters afterward were making progress 
president reagan meanwhile tore into the likely democratic 
presidential nominee as a true liberal bent on more taxing and 
spending 
vice president george bush certain to be the republican 
presidential nominee this fall said the next administration must 
be prepared to seize the opportunity of change in the soviet 
union he said the reagan administrations military buildup had 
helped nudge the soviet union toward openness but he added the 
cold war is not over 
bush made his way from california to wisconsin as a two new 
polls suggested he was closing in his democratic rival the surveys 
stood in contrast to several polls in recent weeks that put 
dukakis lead in double digits 
