<TEXT>
motown records which launched the careers of 
such singers as diana ross michael jackson and stevie wonder and 
won a huge and enduring white audience for black pop music has 
been sold to a unit of entertainment conglomerate mca inc 
the 61 million deal announced tuesday gives mca records the 
famed motown label and rights to a string of hit songs dating back 
to the early 1960s such as i heard it through the grapevine 
and baby love 
mca also will assume motowns current recording contracts with 
such stars as lionel richie smokey robinson and wonder 
berry gordy jr the former detroit auto worker who founded 
motown and built it into what was once the nations biggest 
blackowned business retains the companys sheet music and film 
divisions said motown spokeswoman rosalind stevenson 
mca inc put up 20 percent of the purchase price and boston 
ventures an investment banking firm will supply the remainder 
ms stevenson said the deal calls for mca to buy out boston 
ventures share in the future she said 
mca officials announced the longrumored deal had been completed 
but refused to discuss the terms ms stevenson and another source 
familiar with the talks who refused to be identified confirmed the 
61 million purchase price 
in todays economy the big get bigger and the small get 
extinct gordy said explaining the necessity for the sale in 
tuesdays editions of the entertainment paper daily variety 
in order to prevent that from happening and to ensure the 
perpetuation of motown and its heritage i decided to clasp hands 
with one of the most formidable giants in our business mca 
gordy said 
in the 1960s motown named for its motor town roots in 
detroit discovered and molded a lineup of black recording artists 
and churned out a line of songs that topped pop charts for both 
black and white audiences 
for many the harmonies and images of motowns acts are woven 
into the cultural backdrop of the 1960s diana ross and the 
supremes singing baby love love child and stop in the 
name of love the temptations my girl the four tops i 
cant help myself and marvin gayes i heard it through the 
grapevine 
michael jackson began his musical career with motown as a child 
member of the jackson five 
wonder whose hits on motownallied labels include the 1973 
charttoppers superstition and you are the sunshine of my 
life agreed to stay on under mca before the sale went through 
said the source familiar with the negotiations 
diana ross who in her solo career has recorded with rca signed 
with mca previous to the deal and will return to the motown label 
ms stevenson said 
gordy formed motown in 1960 and moved it to los angles 1971 
gordy who worked as talent scout arranger and producer ran the 
company like a stern father demanding loyalty and also encouraging 
his performers to finish high school though he made it only 
through 11th grade 
privatelyowned motown was the nations most visible black 
business and at one time its biggest last year motown was the 
